I have always loved Einstein Brothers! They aren't very popular where I live now, so when I saw one in Chicago, I was so excited to bring some bagels home. However, my experience there was probably the worst I've ever experienced at ANY establishment, ever, not just Einstein's. This is gonna be a long review... I walked in with my friend, and went up to the "Order Here" sign, next to the bagel display. There were three or four workers behind the counter with their backs turned, making sandwiches and such. That was fine, since I needed time to decide anyway. But after about three minutes of waiting, no one had said a word to me, my friend, or the other customer in line. Finally, one of the ladies told us "You order over there" and pointed to the register. I thought "...ok, well the sign says order here, and this is where the bagels are, but whatever." So I go down to the register, tell her I want half a dozen, and pay. The register girl tells another girl to go get my bagels. I ask if I'm allowed to choose, and she says yes. So I go back to the Order Here area. The girl chosen to help me said that she was new, but based what happens next, I find it hard to believe she received any training at all. So, she awkwardly stands behind the bagel display, not saying anything and looking around. So, I start by saying "Hi, I'll have two chocolate chip bagels, a blueberry, a garlic-..." But I stop because she doesn't appear to be listening, nor is she making any moves to grab a bagel. She says, "Blueberry, what?" At this point I'm really annoyed and tired of being patient with this whole situation, so I decide to do this bagel by bagel. "Two chocolate chip bagels" She looks around the display, searching. Now, I find it hard to believe that there are no signs on the other side of the display indicating the types of bagels in each basket. If there were such signs, she had no idea, because she had to desperately search for each one as I called it out. I had to point out each bagel's location in the display. We continue, and the process takes at least a full minute. So then she sets the bagel box down on the counter and tries to close the top of the box. She clearly has no idea how to close the box correctly. So I tell her I can do it and take my bagel box. Now, one of the reasons I love Einstein's bagels is the chocolate chip bagels. I noticed when she grabbed those two, that she picked one from the Cranberrry side of the basket. I wasn't about to be cheated out of my glorious CC bagels, so I check. Lo and behold, one cranberry and one chocolate chip. So I go back to the counter and explain the situation, and a different girl gives me a chocolate chip bagel. I also noticed when I got home that she gave me a pretzel instead of a potato bagel. Ugh. Thus ends my terrible experience at this Einstein Bros location. I am amazed that they are able to function with such incompetence. Seriously, this location needs to hire higher quality staff, and ensure that they're trained before putting them on the Sunday mid-morning shift. This was an embarressment.

I've tried to eat at this place twice but the service is sooooo slow. The first attempt was two months ago, there were five people ahead of me in line. After waiting ten minutes on only moving up two spots in line I walked out the door.  Today I tried to go back. I walked in about 15 minutes before they closed. There was one other customer and four employees that I could see. Just like the time before, I was not greeted whatsoever. I waited in the order line for a couple minutes and then an employee, who appeared to be a manager that was sitting in the corner working on some paperwork yelled across the seating area to another employee  that they were closing in ten minutes. I thought she was talking to me, but she clarified that she wasn't and went back to her paperwork in the corner.  There were two employees behind the counter but neither acknowledge my presence. They appeared to be cleaning and getting ready to leave. After waiting about five more minutes and not having an employee try to take my order, I walked out and went a couple blocks down the street to NYC Bagel Deli. I'm embarrassed for Einstein that they could care so little about the customer experience. Obviously I wont be going back, and I recommend everyone else do the same.
